Pattern matching with regex, not shell syntax
Will match anywhere on a liine

Find alternatives:
grep 'str1\|str2' filename


options
	-w	match whole words
	-s	dont print access denied messages, etc
	-l  only list matching files
    -A# after context
	-v  exclude match

Matching
    ^/$   beginning/end of line (anchors)

Bracket expressions
    [abc]  match if any character 
    [^abc]  don't match if any 

Character classes
    [:upper:]

Repitition
    *   zero or more times
    extended 
        +       one or more 
        {n}     num of repititions
        {n,n}   range

Grouping
    ()  Enclose group.  Escape if not extended

excluding files under zsh
	grep -irl thing (*~*html)(.)


